titles.title: Designating majority membership on certain standing committees of the House.

vote.text: On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to without objection.

action.text: Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

bill.summary: 1/21/1993--Introduced. Designates majority party membership on the following standing committees of the House of Representatives: (1) Armed Services; (2) Banking, Finance and Urban Affairs; (3) Education and Labor; (4) Foreign Affairs; (5) Government Operations; (6) House Administration; (7) Judiciary; (8) Merchant Marine and Fisheries; (9) Natural Resources; (10) Post Office and Civil Service; (11) Science, Space, and Technology; and (12) Small Business.
